<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2019-12-31</DATELINE><TITLE>How Much Drool Is Too Much?</TITLE><BODY>Abstract A 3-year-old boy presented to the emergency department with a chief complaint of “lethargy” and was found to have ptosis with eventual respiratory failure and need for emergent intubation. There is a broad differential for a patient with respiratory failure, and careful physical examination and history are imperative to reduce morbidity and prevent mortality. After further evaluation and workup, the diagnosis is ultimately revealed.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>